verses.text_plain: The mighty God, even the Lord, hath spoken, and called the earth from the rising of the sun unto the going down thereof.
verses.verse_html:
1The mighty God, even the Lord, hath spoken, and called the earth from the rising of the sun unto the going down thereof. ▼
▼ of…: or, for Asaph

footnotes.body_html: ▼ of…: or, for Asaph

verses.text_plain: Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty, God hath shined.
verses.verse_html: 2Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty, God hath shined.

verses.text_plain: Our God shall come, and shall not keep silence: a fire shall devour before him, and it shall be very tempestuous round about him.
verses.verse_html: 3Our God shall come, and shall not keep silence: a fire shall devour before him, and it shall be very tempestuous round about him.

tokens.text: him, and it shall be very

verses.text_plain: He shall call to the heavens from above, and to the earth, that he may judge his people.
verses.verse_html: 4He shall call to the heavens from above, and to the earth, that he may judge his people.

verses.text_plain: Gather my saints together unto me; those that have made a covenant with me by sacrifice.
verses.verse_html: 5Gather my saints together unto me; those that have made a covenant with me by sacrifice.

tokens.text: together unto me; those that have made

verses.text_plain: And the heavens shall declare his righteousness: for God is judge himself. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 6And the heavens shall declare his righteousness: for God is judge himself. Selah.

verses.text_plain: Hear, O my people, and I will speak; O Israel, and I will testify against thee: I am God, even thy God.
verses.verse_html: 7Hear, O my people, and I will speak; O Israel, and I will testify against thee: I am God, even thy God.

verses.text_plain: I will not reprove thee for thy sacrifices or thy burnt offerings, to have been continually before me.
verses.verse_html: 8I will not reprove thee for thy sacrifices or thy burnt offerings, to have been continually before me.

verses.text_plain: I will take no bullock out of thy house, nor he goats out of thy folds.
verses.verse_html: 9I will take no bullock out of thy house, nor he goats out of thy folds.

verses.text_plain: For every beast of the forest is mine, and the cattle upon a thousand hills.
verses.verse_html: 10For every beast of the forest is mine, and the cattle upon a thousand hills.

verses.text_plain: I know all the fowls of the mountains: and the wild beasts of the field are mine.
verses.verse_html:
11I know all the fowls of the mountains: and the wild beasts of the field are mine. ▼
▼ mine: Heb. with me

footnotes.body_html: ▼ mine: Heb. with me

verses.text_plain: If I were hungry, I would not tell thee: for the world is mine, and the fulness thereof.
verses.verse_html: 12If I were hungry, I would not tell thee: for the world is mine, and the fulness thereof.

verses.text_plain: Will I eat the flesh of bulls, or drink the blood of goats?
verses.verse_html: 13Will I eat the flesh of bulls, or drink the blood of goats?

verses.text_plain: Offer unto God thanksgiving; and pay thy vows unto the most High:
verses.verse_html: 14Offer unto God thanksgiving; and pay thy vows unto the most High:

verses.text_plain: And call upon me in the day of trouble: I will deliver thee, and thou shalt glorify me.
verses.verse_html: 15And call upon me in the day of trouble: I will deliver thee, and thou shalt glorify me.

verses.text_plain: But unto the wicked God saith, What hast thou to do to declare my statutes, or that thou shouldest take my covenant in thy mouth?
verses.verse_html: 16But unto the wicked God saith, What hast thou to do to declare my statutes, or that thou shouldest take my covenant in thy mouth?

tokens.text: What hast thou to do to declare

verses.text_plain: Seeing thou hatest instruction, and castest my words behind thee.
verses.verse_html: 17Seeing thou hatest instruction, and castest my words behind thee.

verses.text_plain: When thou sawest a thief, then thou consentedst with him, and hast been partaker with adulterers.
verses.verse_html:
18When thou sawest a thief, then thou consentedst with him, and hast been partaker with adulterers. ▼
▼ hast…: Heb. thy portion was with

tokens.text: with him, and hast been partaker

footnotes.body_text: ▼ hast…: Heb. thy portion was with
footnotes.body_html: ▼ hast…: Heb. thy portion was with

verses.text_plain: Thou givest thy mouth to evil, and thy tongue frameth deceit.
verses.verse_html:
19Thou givest thy mouth to evil, and thy tongue frameth deceit. ▼
▼ givest: Heb. sendest

verses.text_plain: Thou sittest and speakest against thy brother; thou slanderest thine own mother’s son.
verses.verse_html: 20Thou sittest and speakest against thy brother; thou slanderest thine own mother’s son.

verses.text_plain: These things hast thou done, and I kept silence; thou thoughtest that I was altogether such an one as thyself: but I will reprove thee, and set them in order before thine eyes.
verses.verse_html: 21These things hast thou done, and I kept silence; thou thoughtest that I was altogether such an one as thyself: but I will reprove thee, and set them in order before thine eyes.

verses.text_plain: Now consider this, ye that forget God, lest I tear you in pieces, and there be none to deliver.
verses.verse_html: 22Now consider this, ye that forget God, lest I tear you in pieces, and there be none to deliver.

verses.text_plain: Whoso offereth praise glorifieth me: and to him that ordereth his conversation aright will I shew the salvation of God.
verses.verse_html:
23Whoso offereth praise glorifieth me: and to him that ordereth his conversation aright will I shew the salvation of God. ▼
